New Hel.fi

Citizen-centric renewal of the largest website in Finland

Services

UI/UX Design Design Leadership

Client

City of Helsinki

Year

2020-2022

Background

Old ways won't open new doors

The city of Helsinki's hel.fi was serving as one of the largest websites in Finland. However, it needed a comprehensive renewal to meet modern web standards and user expectations. This project aimed to create a more user-friendly and accessible digital presence for the city.

Approach

Translating the Helsinki brand into a digital experience

Digital Brand Experience

We created a cohesive digital brand experience that aligns with Helsinki's visual identity.

Building a Solid Design System

We developed a comprehensive design system to ensure consistency across all digital touchpoints.

Rapid Prototyping and User Testing

We employed iterative design processes with frequent user testing to refine the user experience.

Solution

Integrating design into the city organization

The journey to create the whole hel.fi is ongoing and will altogether take more than two years. The scale of the project is so massive that the City of Helsinki's own design team has grown significantly during the process.

"This new website has created the new visual and UI concept for city of Helsinki's main website and helped us to build our brand experience in the digital world. We have also been able to create new design capabilities inside the city organization by hiring and training our inhouse designers. This is in practice with documentation and training materials that helps our designers to create cohesive and accessible services."

Pekka Sauri, Deputy Mayor, City of Helsinki
